e happened to be the good month (+\u20b94,997); the March\u2013May stretch more than gave it back. This is exactly why one month is a thin sample \u2014 you saw the favorable slice.\n- **Coin-flip win rate (51.8%)** with a much bigger drawdown (\u2212\u20b940k) tells the story: the 25% stop gets whipsawed. On short straddles, a tight stop repeatedly locks in losses when premium spikes intraday and then mean-reverts \u2014 you get stopped out right before the move you were positioned for.\n- **Drawdown is ~16% of margin** and dwarfs the total P&L, so risk-adjusted this is poor as-is.\n\n**What's worth testing next (pick one):**\n1. **Sweep the stop-loss** (e.g. 25/35/50% + no-stop) \u2014 a looser stop often survives the whipsaws better on straddles.\n2. **Add move-SL-to-cost** after a favorable move, so winners don't turn into losers instead of using a hard stop.\n3. **Whole-strategy MTM target/stop** instead of per-leg \u2014 your June run with a \u20b93,000 target did better.\n\nI'd start with the stop-loss sweep since that's the variable you're questioning. Want me to run 25/35/50% plus a no-stop baseline over the full period?", "results": [{"label": "Custom position", "res": {"strategy": "Custom position", "metrics": {"n": 56, "win": 51.8, "avgw": 1.12, "avgl": -1.28, "pf": 0.94, "exp": -0.04, "avg_bars": 1.0}, "performance": {"equity_curve": [{"date": "2026-03-30", "equity": 244191.0}, {"date": "2026-04-01", "equity": 245622.0}, {"date": "2026-04-02", "equity": 252770.0}, {"date": "2026-04-13", "equity": 257741.0}, {"date": "2026-04-15", "equity": 254824.0}, {"date": "2026-04-16", "equity": 256817.0}, {"date": "2026-04-17", "equity": 259402.0}, {"date": "2026-04-20", "equity": 258567.0}, {"date": "2026-04-21", "equity": 261603.0}, {"date": "2026-04-22", "equity": 260379.0}, {"date": "2026-04-23", "equity": 257451.0}, {"date": "2026-04-24", "equity": 261178.0}, {"date": "2026-04-27", "equity": 262311.0}, {"date": "2026-04-28", "equity": 260389.0}, {"date": "2026